 Machine Learning-Based Blood Cancer Detection

📌 Project Overview

This project focuses on detecting hematological malignancies using machine learning techniques based on Complete Blood Count (CBC) parameters.

📊 Dataset

* Source: Mendeley Data
* Features include WBC, RBC, Hemoglobin, Platelets, etc.
* A target variable (Diagnosis) was engineered using clinically relevant thresholds.

⚙️ Methodology

1. Data preprocessing and cleaning
2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
3. Feature engineering (Diagnosis creation)
4. Feature scaling
5. Model training using:

   * Logistic Regression
   * Decision Tree
   * Support Vector Machine
   * Random Forest
6. Model evaluation using accuracy, confusion matrix, and classification report

⚠️ Important Note

To avoid data leakage, features used in label creation were removed before model training.

📈 Results

* Achieved realistic accuracy using Random Forest
* Validated using cross-validation

🚀 Technologies Used

* Python
* Pandas, NumPy
* Scikit-learn
* Matplotlib, Seaborn

🎯 Conclusion

Machine learning can effectively analyze hematological parameters to support early detection of blood cancer.

